          "merged_at": null
        },
        "body": "Summary:\r\n- Fixes missing implementations for lineTo and qcurveTo in [getMinMaxXYFromCurvePathOps](vscode-file://vscode-app/Applications/Visual%20Studio%20Code.app/Contents/Resources/app/out/vs/code/electron-browser/workbench/workbench.html), and adds a helper to compute axis-aligned bounds for quadratic Bézier segments.\r\n- Addresses issue #10366.\r\n\r\nWhat I did:\r\n- Modified [bounds.ts](vscode-file://vscode-app/Applications/Visual%20Studio%20Code.app/Contents/Resources/app/out/vs/code/electron-browser/workbench/workbench.html):\r\nAdded [getQuadraticBezierCurveBound(p0, p1, p2)](vscode-file://vscode-app/Applications/Visual%20Studio%20Code.app/Contents/Resources/app/out/vs/code/electron-browser/workbench/workbench.html) to compute min/max for x and y of quadratic Bézier curves.\r\nImplemented the lineTo branch in [getMinMaxXYFromCurvePathOps](vscode-file://vscode-app/Applications/Visual%20Studio%20Code.app/Contents/Resources/app/out/vs/code/electron-browser/workbench/workbench.html) to include segment endpoints in bounds calculation.\r\nImplemented the qcurveTo branch to compute bounds for quadratic curves and fold them into the accumulated limits.\r\n- No public API changes.\r\n\r\nWhy??:\r\n[getMinMaxXYFromCurvePathOps](vscode-file://vscode-app/Applications/Visual%20Studio%20Code.app/Contents/Resources/app/out/vs/code/electron-browser/workbench/workbench.html) previously had TODOs for lineTo and qcurveTo, causing incorrect/missing bounding boxes for elements based on straight segments or quadratic curves (reported in #10366). The change ensures correct axis-aligned bounding boxes are returned for these drawable ops.\r\n",
